{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In a major update and enhancement to its native scripting language, OS X delivers a new plugin architecture for AppleScript, enabling easy development and access to custom sets of functions and methods. Each individual AppleScript Library, saved as an AppleScript script file, can publish its own scripting terminology, and contain dozens of routines written in native AppleScript or the incredibly powerful AppleScriptObjective-C. Scripting just got a whole lot better!"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Read Transcript","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2013\/416\/","type":"reference"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC13"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC13-416-Introducing-AppleScript-Libraries","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc13-416-introducing-applescript-libraries"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC13","title":"Introducing AppleScript Libraries","role":"sampleCode"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC13":{"title":"WWDC13","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc13","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/doc